post_text:
Warrenton Hammond School District Community:

The Warrenton Hammond School District just received notice from Pacific Power that there will be a planned power outage starting today at 11 AM. There will be no power to the Warrenton Grade School and Warrenton High School campuses.

Because we are not able to operate school safely without power, we will have an emergency early dismissal today.

Our official dismissal time today is now 11:15 AM. All bus routes will be in operation.

Parents are invited to pick-up their children before 11 AM.

The grade school staff will contact or have students contact their parents before the students are dismissed.

Tom Rogozinski
Superintendent

The Warrenton-Hammond School Board would like to invite you to attend the board work session Wednesday, December 19th at 5:00 in the WHS Library.

During the work session the school board will be sharing the Superintendent Search process with the public and also welcome input from parents, students, staff, and the general public on what they would like to see in the new superintendent of the Warrenton-Hammond School District.

If you have any questions please contact the District Office for more information. 503-861-2281

post_text:
This morning, December 11, 2018, Warrenton Grade School administrators were notified a student had an alleged hazardous substance made from household cleaning supplies in a backpack at school. They contacted the student and secured the backpack. The Warrenton Police Department, a Hazmat team, and the Warrenton Fire Department responded and took possession of the backpack.
The Warrenton Police Department is currently conducting an investigation of this incident. The district is conducting a separate investigation related to potential disciplinary action.

post_text: This November, the Warrenton School Board is putting forward a construction bond as part of long-term vision for our local schools. Our schools need improvements in safety and security – including staged construction of schools outside the tsunami inundation zone. With future growth projections over of the next decade, addressing overcrowding is a priority. The Warrenton School District is doing everything we can to give our students a competitive edge with career and vocational programs. To learn more visit www.warrenton-hammondschoolbond.org.
